programme.desc: In this serial, a criminal called "The Spider" puts Dick Tracy's brother under a hypnotic trance and turns him against the famous detective.

programme.title: Brothers United
programme.desc: In this serial, a criminal called "The Spider" puts Dick Tracy's brother under a hypnotic trance and turns him against the famous detective.

programme.title: Something To Sing About (1937)
programme.desc: "Something To Sing About" is the high-spirited account of Terry Rooney (James Cagney), a popular band leader with an offer to work in Hollywood. But nothing is ever easy in show business; Rooney learns that being famous is just as troublesome as being unknown. This colorful, comical film was directed by Victor Schertzinger ("The Road to Zanzibar," "The Road to Singapore") who also wrote the movie’s many songs. The movie also features a superb supporting cast which includes William Frawley ("I Love Lucy"), and Dwight Fry ("Dracula").

programme.title: Sitting on the Moon (1936)
programme.desc: In a misguided and selfish attempt to rekindle the career of the lovely fading movie star Polly, songwriter Danny promptly ends his long standing partnership with his lyricist, Mike. Not content to take the injustice lying down, the dejected Mike sends in a blonde seductress to try and break up Polly and the smitten Danny. With three-time Oscar nominee Ralph Staub taking the reins behind the camera, the rousing, crowd-pleasing Sitting on the Moon is a roaring good time for the whole family. Featuring typically solid turns from B-movie musical crooner Roger Pryor (Belle of the Nineties) and Broadway mainstay Pert Kelton (The Music Man), performing the film's six original musical numbers with gusto to spare.

programme.title: I'm From Arkansas (1944)
programme.desc: Welcome to Pitchfork, Arkansas, where proud farmer Juniper Jenkins is celebrating his prize hog Esmeralda giving birth to 18 piglets. The event attracts many tourists and real life country musicians to Pitchfork, including Mary Ford, Merle Travis, Jimmy Wakely, and countless others. Starring as Farmer Jenkins is Slim Summerville, a former Keystone Cop who became one of Hollywood's most reliable journeyman, appearing in everything from Charlie Chan and Shirley Temple movies, to the classic All Quiet on the Western Front.

programme.title: Buffalo Stampede
programme.desc: Randolph Scott plays a Buffalo hide trader on a mission of the heart in this adaptation based on Zane Grey's The Thundering Herd.

programme.title: The Joe Louis Story (1953)
programme.desc: Legendary boxing champion Joe Louis is the subject of this biopic from director Robert Gordon (It Came from Beneath the Sea, Tarzan and the Jungle Boy). Former amateur boxing star Coley Wallace stars as the champ, while the rest of the cast includes John Manley, Hilda Sims, and film noir favorite, Paul Stewart. Of interest to boxing fans, the film features actual footage of many classic Louis bouts, including his battles with Max Baer, Jimmy Braddock, and Primo Carnera!

programme.title: Sundowners (1950)
programme.desc: Brother battles brother in this gritty tale of feuding ranchers in the old west. This story of the Texas panhandle stars such familiar faces as Robert Preston, Chill Wills, and Jack Elam, and was a rare film for its time in that it was filmed almost entirely in Texas with no studio interiors. If for no other reason, watch this one for Preston’s performance. If you only know him from The Music Man or Victor Victoria, you’re sure to be surprised here!

programme.title: Father's Little Dividend
programme.desc: Spencer Tracy and Elizabeth Taylor reprise their father/daughter roles in this sequel to the popular Father of the Bride. This time around Stanley Banks (Tracy) finds himself resisting the idea of becoming a grandfather, and soon finds himself in a series of comical misadventures involving his new grandson. Legendary directory Vincente Minnelli shot this charming family film in a mere 22 days in 1950, the same year he directed his classic An American in Paris. The cast includes Joan Bennett, Billie Burke, and a 14-year-old Russ Tamblyn.

programme.title: Port of New York (1949)
programme.desc: Movie icon Yul Brynner made his debut in this tough crime thriller from director Laslo Benedek (The Wild One). Brynner plays ruthless gangster Paul Vicola, a murderous thug whose gang has stolen medicinal narcotics from a ship docked in New York harbor. The movie also stars Scott Brady and Richard Rober as the agents out to stop Vicola, a dangerous assignment since Vicola is the sort who will have his own girlfriend killed if he thinks she knows too much!

programme.title: Attack of the Mayan Mummy
programme.desc: Following the death of his sister, who was co-director with him of the Cowan Research Center in Pasadena, Dr. Frederick Munson was ousted and replaced by his widowed brother-in-law, Dr. Edmund Redding. Through Redding's son, Timmy, Munson has been able to learn of a secret project at the institute involving the use of hypnosis to regress subjects to past lives, which information Munson passes along to a friend, Dr. John Janney. (BW)

programme.title: The Flaming Urge
programme.desc: Harold Lloyd Jr. stars as Tom Smith, the newest resident of a small town, with the peculiar habit of observing fires. When a series of arson attacks begin popping up in town, Smith is pegged as the primary suspect. Also starring Cathy Downs, Byron Foulger, and Jonathan Hale.

programme.title: Killer Kowalski vs. Yukon Eric
programme.desc: Killer Kowalski faces off against Yukon Eric.

programme.title: Night Tide
programme.desc: A young sailor falls in love with a mysterious woman, performing as a mermaid at the local carnival. He soon comes to suspect the girl might be a real mermaid, who draws men to a watery death during the full moon.

programme.title: The Monster Walks (1932)
programme.desc: Trapped in a house on a dark, stormy night with a killer ape! Returning to her recently deceased father’s sizable estate to read his last will and testament, Ruth Earlton (Vera Reynolds) and her fiancé are horrified to discover that the basement is occupied by a massive, hideous ape that was subjected to experimentation by her father. And although Ruth is given control of her late father’s estate, she soon finds herself the prime target of the mutated simian—and possibly the nefarious housekeepers, bitter about their meager share of their former master’s fortune. Featuring a compelling turn from Oscar Nominee Mischa Auer (My Man Godfrey) and helmed by genre B-Movie maestro Frank R. Strayer (The Vampire Bat), The Monster Walks is a chilling and mysterious master class in eeriness.

programme.title: Man Beast
programme.desc: Connie Hayward mounts an expedition into the Himalayan Mountains looking for her brother, who has not returned from a previous trek trying to locate the Yeti, or "Abominable Snowman". Arriving at her brother's last-known camp Connie and her companions find only a strange old guide, Varga. They are soon attacked by gigantic Snowmen but are not half as surprised as when Vargas reveals his secret origin and the plans he has for Connie.

programme.title: Invisible Ghost (1941)
programme.desc: Bela Lugosi headlines this creepy thriller about an influential man who becomes a bloodthirsty maniac after his wife deserts him. It was the first of nine films made by Lugosi for Sam Katzman of Monogram Pictures, but it’s director Joseph H. Lewis (Gun Crazy, The Big Combo) who elevates this low budget potboiler into something memorable. Aided by veteran cinematographers Harvey Gould and Marcel Le Picard, Lewis creates the perfect atmosphere for this tale of a murderer who strikes in the night and leaves no clues...

programme.title: Man in the Attic (1953)
programme.desc: Jack Palance stars as a mysterious man suspected of being the notorious Jack the Ripper! Palance plays a research pathologist in 1888 London, seeking to rent a quiet attic room for his “experiments.”

programme.title: Door (1956)
programme.desc: Here he is: the one, the only… GROUCHO! Legendary comedian, Groucho Marx, hosts this laugh-a-minute quiz show, where three couples face off, answering questions of varying difficulty. This game show is sure to make you laugh as contestants struggle to keep up with Marx’s lightning-quick wit and goofy antics.

programme.title: The Big Net (1956)
programme.desc: Friday and Smith attempt to stop a robber accused of assaulting and robbing women.

programme.title: The Forests of the Night
programme.desc: While on a hunting trip, three friends find a mysterious Chinese game that promises to make a man what he is not. The three friends play the game and soon notice one of their friends is acting strangely.

programme.title: The Picture War (1960)
programme.desc: Mike and his camera set out to catch a killer after several witnesses to the murder begin getting into strange “accidents.”

programme.title: Brad's Class Reunion
programme.desc: In an effort to stop Brad from reuniting with an ex girlfriend, Joan tries to keep him away from his class reunion.

programme.title: The Savage
programme.desc: After Adam gets hurt while saving a woman from a group of indians, the woman must nurse Adam back to health as the rest of the tribe sets out to find her.

programme.title: Elly Becomes a Secretary
programme.desc: Mr. Drysdale has to speak at a conference while Miss Hathaway is out sick, so Jed helps out by running the bank and appoints Elly to be his secretary.

programme.title: The Executive
programme.desc: Mickey becomes insecure when he realizes that his short size may be impeding his growth in the business world.

programme.title: The Case of the Cunningham Heritage (1954)
programme.desc: Watson meets Sherlock Holmes, and assists him in solving a case that has left Inspector Lestrade puzzled.

programme.title: Awake to Spring
programme.desc: Medic follows Dr. Konrad Styner and his team of Surgeons as they tackle medical cases inside Los Angeles.

programme.title: The Billy Grimes Story
programme.desc: New York City police officer Barney Ruditsky faces off against organized crime during the Roaring 20s.

programme.title: and Mr. Phillips' Plot
programme.desc: Stanley is forced to play matchmaker for Mr. Phillips who likes the florist working at the hotel.

programme.title: Bud's Encounter with the Law
programme.desc: Kathy gets carried away with the new washing machine and ends up ruining the valuables of Betty and Bud.

programme.title: Retreat and Decision
programme.desc: Jesus withdraws with the twelve to lands outside Herod's jurisdiction. The disciples know it is a critical period in the Master's life, He reveals now that they are the Church, predicts His death and resurrection. Peter, James and John witness Christ's transfiguration, Jesus heals the epileptic boy, blesses little children, and raises Lazarus from the dead, Jesus' triumphal entry to Jerusalem is halted at the Temple gates when He sees the money changers in the Temple courtyard.

programme.title: Africa Screams (1949)
programme.desc: Bud Abbott and Lou Costello are a pair of mild-mannered bookworms who pose as big game hunters travelling deep into the African jungle in search of a rare gorilla - but what's really at stake is a secret diamond mine. Along the way they'll tangle with lions, cannibals, criminals, and, of course, wild apes! Their accomplices include the lovely Hillary Brooke (who later appeared on their TV series) and Three Stooges co-horts Shemp Howard and Joe Besser - plus, cameos from real-life lion tamer Clyde Beatty and bug-game tracker Frank Buck.

programme.title: Swing High Swing Low
programme.desc: Fred MacMurray and Carole Lombard star in this tale of a swingin’ trumpet player and the women who love him. Anthony Quinn, Franklin Pangborn, and Dorothy Lamour also appear in this feature from director Mitchell Leisen (Hold Back the Dawn, The Big Broadcast of 1938). Songs include "Then It Isn’t Love" by the Oscar nominated songwriting team of Leo Robin and Ralph Rainger, plus several numbers sung by Lamour, who was just beginning her career but nearly steals the show from the more experienced team of Lombard and MacMurray.

programme.title: Doll Face (1945)
programme.desc: Burlesque queen Doll Face Carroll (Vivian Blaine) is dismissed from a Broadway show because she's considered crude. Her manager suggests she get some publicity by writing her memoirs, but the ghost writer he hires to help has more on his mind than writing books. With a cast that includes Dennis O'Keefe, Perry Como, and Carmen Miranda, this little jewel from director Lewis Seiler (Charlie Chan in Paris) was based on a play by the burlesque legend, Gypsy Rose Lee. Also, look for an appearance by Brazil's Bando da Lua as Carmen Miranda's orchestra!

programme.title: One-Eyed Jacks
programme.desc: Dad Longworth robs a Mexican bank, takes the loot, and leaves his partner Rio to be captured. However, Rio escapes capture and searches for Dad in California.

programme.title: Gomez vs McShane
programme.desc: Gomez faces off against McShane.

programme.title: Island Claws
programme.desc: When a biological experiment goes terribly wrong, scientists unleash a legion of giant killer crabs.

programme.title: Ilio DiPaolo vs Hans Schmidt
programme.desc: In this match, Llio DiPaolo faces off against Hans Schmidt.

programme.title: Carol Burnett Show - Season 1 Episode 12
programme.desc: Carol Burnett stars in a series of comedic sketches guest starring Barbara Eden, and Leonard Nimoy.

programme.title: Season 19 Episode 39
programme.desc: Comedian Johnny Carson hosts a variety of celebrities in his iconic late night talk show.

programme.title: Murder By Television (1935)
programme.desc: When the inventor of a new method of sending television signals refuses to sell his ideas to television companies, he turns up dead! Bela Lugosi stars (and is the prime suspect) in this perfect story of a perfect crime.

programme.title: Long Hair of Death
programme.desc: In a 15th-century feudal village, a woman is accused of witchcraft and put to death. Her beautiful older daughter knows the real reason for the execution lies in the lord's sexual desire for her mother. After confronting the lord on the matter, she, too, is killed. A much younger daughter is spared and taken in by her mother's killers. Once she is of age, as a horrible, deadly plague sweeps the land, she marries the lord's worthless son. Then, during a brutal thunderstorm, the older daughter mysteriously reappears and begins to avenge her mother's death.

programme.title: Brother, Cry for Me
programme.desc: Three brothers searching for Inca treasure resort to kidnapping, extortion and murder in this independent thriller. Starring Steve Drexel, Larry Parnell, and Leslie Parrish...

programme.title: Drive-In Massacre
programme.desc: You'll Pay To Get In... And Pray To Get Out! Two detectives are hell-bent on capturing a demented killer who has been stalking a California drive-in! The film's original poster featured the following: "DRIVE-IN MASSACRE has been deemed by an independent film board to be too terrifying for viewing by the average theatre patron. For this reason, it is suggested that those of you with severe emotional disorders or chronic coronary dysfunction NOT see this movie. The risk is entirely yours." You can't say you haven't been warned!

programme.title: The Vampire Bat (1933)
programme.desc: An excellent cast featuring Lionel Atwill, Fay Wray, Melvyn Douglas, and the immortal Dwight Frye headline this macabre tale of vampire attacks in a small village. Does a troubled man-child with an affection for bats have something to do with it? Or is it a local scientist who appears to know quite a bit about vampirism? Director Frank R. Strayer spins a thrilling tale from Hugo nominated screenwriter Edward T. Lowe (House of Frankenstein, House of Dracula) and will have you craving more films from the first golden age of horror!

programme.title: Food (1955)
programme.desc: Here he is: the one, the only… GROUCHO! Legendary comedian, Groucho Marx, hosts this laugh-a-minute quiz show, where three couples face off, answering questions of varying difficulty. This game show is sure to make you laugh as contestants struggle to keep up with Marx’s lightning-quick wit and goofy antics.

programme.title: The Big Little Jesus (1953)
programme.desc: It's Christmas Eve when Father Rojas at the Old Mission Plaza Church in Los Angeles discovers that the statue of the Infant Jesus is stolen from the crib. The statue's worth is only a few dollars, but it is of great sentimental value for the parish. Friday and Smith promise to try to get it back before mass on Christmas Day, but this means that they have less than 24 hours to catch the thief.

programme.title: Who Are You?
programme.desc: While recovering from scarlet fever, Laurie Warren travels to the home of Mr. and Mrs. Mason, a couple who have recently lost their daughter. Laurie imagines she is their daughter, going so far as to reject her parents when they come for her. Things change, however, when Mrs. Mason finds out she is pregnant and Laurie goes back to her old self.

programme.title: Touch Off (1960)
programme.desc: Mike goes undercover as a firebug in an attempt to take down a ring of arsonists.

programme.title: Hunting
programme.desc: Joan finds a way to join Brad and his friends on their camping trip.

programme.title: The Mill
programme.desc: With Tom Edwards’ ranch going to waste since his becoming a paraplegic following an accident with Ben, Ben makes a business proposition: The Cartwrights will build a mill on Edwards’ land. In return, Ben requests that he earn his investment money back as well as fifteen percent. The deal is made, but suspicions of Edwards’ accident bring tension to Ponderosa and put their agreement at risk.

programme.title: Jethro's Friend
programme.desc: Jethro has Armstrong Dueser McHugh III over to the house, who is coddled and treated like he's frail by a chauffeur.

programme.title: Till the Song is Done, till the Dance Is Gone
programme.desc: Medic follows Dr. Konrad Styner and his team of Surgeons as they tackle medical cases inside Los Angeles.

programme.title: The Sonny Rosen Story
programme.desc: New York City police officer Barney Ruditsky faces off against organized crime during the Roaring 20s.

programme.title: Married Friends
programme.desc: Stanley and Celia consider their future together as they meet up with their married friends.

programme.title: Thanksgiving Day
programme.desc: Kathy writes a poem for a school project and is chosen as the winner in her class. However, when she reads the poem to her parents, Jim is critical.

programme.title: Intimate Interviews - James Cagney
programme.desc: 1931 interview with James Cagney.

programme.title: Here's Flash Casey (1938)
programme.desc: Young Flash finds life in the newspaper world more demanding than his years as a college photographer. Whether he’s snapping photos of a big shot who doesn’t want his picture taken, or trying to romance a sexy society columnist, Flash is always one step away from trouble. Starring Eric Linden as the always upbeat Flash, this Poverty Row feature from director Lynn Shores (Charlie Chan at the Wax Museum) pays tribute to all of the daredevil cameramen who risked their necks for a front page scoop!

programme.title: The Bank
programme.desc: Charlie Chaplin stars as a love struck janitor of a bank. Heartbroken after realizing his love is unrequited, Charlie dreams of saving Edna the secretary during a Bank robbery.

programme.title: The Bob Hope Show: The First Overseas Tour Show
programme.desc: Actor, stand-up comedian, and host extraordinaire Bob Hope takes the lead on his first overseas tour show, featuring special guests Marilyn Maxwell, Jimmy Wakely, and Judy Kelly.

programme.title: Glorifying the American Girl
programme.desc: Mary Eaton stars in this rollicking feature about the rise of a showgirl. This early talkie includes cameos by many of the top names of the day, including Rudy Vallee, Eddie Cantor, Irving Berlin, and Ring Lardner, and culminates with a Ziegfeld Follies dance number! Also, listen for such period hits as 'Bye Bye Blackbird', 'Baby Face', and 'Blue Skies'. This movie is like a time machine, and it will take you back!

programme.title: Salem and the Scarlet Letter
programme.desc: Originally filmed in 1980 with location footage of Salem, this stunning documentary provides a historic look at the city of Salem and one of its best remembered residents, Nathaniel Hawthorne. Written and directed by legendary independent filmmaker Samuel M. Sherman, with narration from prolific character actor John Carradine

programme.title: McLintock
programme.desc: He likes his whiskey hard... His women soft... And his west all to himself! Inspired by Shakespeare’s “The Taming of the Shrew” (1594), John Wayne (The Searchers, Stagecoach), Maureen O’Hara (Miracle on 34th Street, The Parent Trap), and Patrick Wayne (The Searchers, The Alamo) star in this western comedy directed by Andrew V. McLaglen (Gunsmoke, The Wild Geese). George Washington McLintock (John Wayne) is the wealthiest man in his territory who utilizes his power and influence to maintain order between farmers, ranchers, Indians, corrupt government officials, and his own family! McLintock is McNificent!

programme.title: Secrets of a Sorority Girl
programme.desc: A group of gamblers blackmail the district attorney claiming they will release pictures of his daughter drinking and playing roulette.

programme.title: Devil's Daughter
programme.desc: Sylvia Walton returns from Harlem to take over a Jamaican plantation from her vindictive half-sister, amid the growing sound of drums.

programme.title: Larry Shane vs. Bobby Nelson
programme.desc: In this match, Larry Shane fights Bobby Nelson.

programme.title: Carol Burnett Show - Season 1 Episode 13
programme.desc: Carol Burnett hosts guest stars Mickey Rooney and John Davidson in a series of comedy sketches.

programme.title: Season 25 Episode 65
programme.desc: Comedian Johnny Carson hosts a variety of celebrities in his iconic late night talk show.

programme.title: Angelo Poffo vs Jerry Christy
programme.desc: In this match, Angelo Poffo faces off against Jerry Christy.

programme.title: Pat O’Connor vs. Legs Langevin
programme.desc: Pat O'Connor fights Legs Langevin.

programme.title: She Gods of Shark Reef
programme.desc: Two brothers, including one wanted for murder, are shipwrecked on an island inhabited by beautiful woman who possess a cache of valuable pearls. What the brothers don't know is that the island women worship a shark god, and are known to make human sacrifices! With a cast that includes the smoldering Lisa Montell, this intense adventure was directed by drive-in movie king Roger Corman. For movie buffs: Corman made the most of location shooting, filming Shark Reef in the same Hawaiian setting as Naked Paradise (1957).

programme.title: Meet the Patels
programme.desc: In this real-life "My Big Fat Greek Wedding,” an Indian-American man gets help from his parents and extended family so he can start looking for a wife the traditional Indian way.

programme.desc: Academy Award-winning filmmaker Daniel Junge and producer Johnny Knoxville examine the life, career, and legacy of Evel Knievel, the man from Montana who stared death in the face to become a legendary daredevil and heroic icon.

programme.desc: The circus is in town and just in time for National Coming Out Day! Welcome to the 2021 QueerX Awards brought to you by Lexus. Join us as hosts, Drew Droege and Raneir Pollard, take us on a carnival tour of LGBTQ music, films, and icons! Featuring appearances by Bowen Yang, Michaela Jaé Rodriguez, Patton Oswalt, Dwyane Wade, Erica Wheeler, and Elvira, Mistress of the Dark, Cassandra Peterson. And don’t miss the special performances by Chanel and the Circus, Mila Jam, and Alsace Carcione.

programme.title: Culture Q
programme.desc: S1 E23 | We spolight queer talent Jasmin Savory-Brown in the upcoming Scream film, as well Jamie Clayton as Pinhead in Spyglass Media Group's Hellraiser. Later we sit down to chat with Chanel and the Circus, and then discuss the Texas House of Representives passing the anti-trans HB25, attempting to ban trans youth from organized sports. NFL Las Vegas Raiders head coach Jon Gruden, resigns in disgrace amid homophbic email scandal, and out player Carl Nassib takes a rare personal day to process the news. Finally, we celebrate icon and astronaut, Sally Ride who will be the first LGBTQ person featured on US currency, and congratulate Lance Bass and his husband Michael Turchin on the birth of their twins.

programme.title: Voguing The Message
programme.desc: A pre-Madonna primer that raises questions about race, sex and subcultural style, Voguing: The Message traces the roots of this gay Black and Latino dance form, which appropriates and plays with poses and images from mainstream fashion.

programme.title: Gay Mean Girls
programme.desc: S1 E1-2 | Lucy is a “very good ally” who stares at her best friend Miranda…. a lot. They hatch a plan to start Gay Prom Royalty together to promote equality at their school. Miranda pays Lucy a visit on a day off from school. We get a glimpse into Lucy’s home life.

programme.title: Jobriath A.D.
programme.desc: Known as the first openly gay rock star, Jobriath’s reign was a brief two years. Done in by over-hyped publicity, shunned by the gay community, and dismissed by critics, Jobriath retreated to the Chelsea Hotel, where he died forgotten, one of the earliest casualties of AIDS. But years later, new fans discover his music, and acts such as The Pet Shop Boys, Def Leppard, and Morrissey cite him as an influence. Experience the heartbreaking, unbelievable story of the one, the only, Jobriath.

programme.title: Why Can't I Be Me? Around You
programme.desc: Rusty Tidenberg, drag-racing aficionado, shocked friends and family by coming out as trans. Followed for 8 years by filmmaker Harrod Blank (son of Les Blank), Rusty guides us through the aftermath of her transition. Interwoven with lively tales of gender non-conforming individuals on the art-car circuit, Blank’s film is a sensitive and unpredictable love letter to people who fight to be unapologetically themselves.

programme.title: The Millennial Experience
programme.desc: The Millennial Experience is one part dance-for-film and one part documentary. The film explores cultural appropriation vs appreciation, LGBTQIA+ culture, feminism and how these topics impact the Millennial generation. The dance sequences in the film are adapted from director Alex Crozier's stage production MILLENNIALS which focuses on the aforementioned themes. Fourteen on-camera interviews that expound on the main topics were conducted with people of various ages, ethnicities, sexual orientations, and genders . The Millennial Experience seeks to uplift the voices of women, LGBTQIA+, and BIPOC communities in an effort to create a more equitable and just world.

programme.title: My Trans Life
programme.desc: Being trans is a mental, physical and emotional journey and MY TRANS LIFE showcases inspiring trans individuals on their journeys of acceptance. From preparing for major surgery, to tackling love lives, to campaigning for equality, MY TRANS LIFE follows transgender people facing the world in the body they were meant to be in.

programme.title: Political Animals
programme.desc: Political Animals celebrates the legendary civil rights victories of four trailblazing California state politicians: Carole Migden, Sheila Keuhl, Jackie Goldberg, and Christine Kehoe. Fierce and unrelenting, these courageous women toppled a partisan majority and emerged victors to pass historic legislation for social justice and LGBT+ equality. It was a hard fight – filled with vehemently heated debates and hateful insults hurled by opponents. Today, the message behind Political Animals is more important than ever as the current political theatre unfurls around the globe. These inspiring biographies further reveal the critical importance for public resistance at the local level to pressure lawmakers to enact difficult change. Political Animals is a clear call to action for a new era of greater democratic participation. We invite you to follow in the footsteps of these historic leaders and become the next pioneering political animal!

programme.title: Is Written
programme.desc: The story of a poor boy whose biggest dream is to be a filmmaker. A trajectory of sufferings, struggles, victories and defeats. This story comes to show us that dreams are untouchable and worth fighting for.

Dr. Mike Hart is back to chat again with us about that report on MDMA-Assisted therapy for severe PTSD. Dr. Hart is the Host of Heart to Hart Podcast and a medical doctor at the Ready To Go Clinic in London, Ontario. - Here’s some highlights from the interview: - - PTSD very difficult to treat - - Hart says that MDMA-Assisted therapy works because the psychedelic reduces ego - - Hart feels legalization within a year unlikely, and other MDMA-assisted therapy studies will improve

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Actor & Comedian Aries Spear
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is actor comedian Aries Spears. From TV to film, actor Aries Spears spends some time with DL and Jasmine to talk about recent issues with Mike Epps and a social media post about black on black crime versus police racism against blacks.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Actor Miguel A. Nunez
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is actor Miguel Nunez. From TV to film, actor Miguel Nunez spends some time with DL and Jasmine to talk about his career, life as a black actor and discuss some of the issues of today.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Alonzo Bodden
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is standup comedian and former “Last Comic Standing” champion Alonzo Bodden. DL and Alonzo discuss the issues of the pandemic and working as entertainers. They also discuss politics, racism, and other issues in the black community.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Atty Ben Crump
programme.desc: DL Hughley Uncut on GFNTV. Guest on DL Uncut is Civil Rights Attorney Benjamin Crump. Attorney Crump is best known for taking on the toughest cases with national civil rights implications. From Trayvon Martin to Michael Brown, Crump continues to push the envelope for justice for those whose lives have been changed due an unfair legal system.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Charlamagne Tha God
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is one of the hosts on the nationally syndicated radio show The Breakfast Club – Charlamagne Tha God.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest David A. Arnold
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is stand-up comedian, writer and producer David Arnold. He has a special on Netflix called “Fat Ballerina”.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest DJ Doug E. Fresh
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Hughley Uncut is legendary DJ and Hip Hop pioneer Doug E. Fresh. Chris Spencer, the creator of the Real Husbands of Hollywood spends some time with DL and Jasmine to talk about his recent projects and working during a pandemic.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Erika Alexander
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is the brilliant actress from “The Cosby Show” and the 90’s hit series “Living Single” – Erika Alexander. Erika is a producer on the upcoming documentary “John Lewis: Good Trouble” which will release on July 3. DL, Jasmine, and Erika have a great discussion about the creating of “Living Single” and how the show “Friends” became a bigger hit after using the same concept. Erika gives great insight into racism in the entertainment industry.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Leonard Pitts
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is Pulitzer Prize Winner and columnist for the Miami Herald Leonard Pitts, Jr. Leonard Pitts has a progressive voice in journalism who dives deep into the racial and cultural issues of society.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Matt Barnes
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is former NBA star and 2017 NBA Champion Matt Barnes. Matt discusses his upbringing, thoughts on now legalized marijuana. Matt also gives his thoughts on George Floyd and the affects on our society.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Tamika Mallory
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is activist and the former chair of the Women’s March Tamika Mallory. Currently she is the co-founder of the social justice organization Until Freedom. DL, Jasmine, and Tamika share a deep discussion of the after effects of George Floyd’s murder by police, protests, and where civil unrest is headed in America.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Willy T Ribbs
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is former race car driver Willy T. Ribbs. Willy was the first African American to test a Formula One racing car and first African American to compete in the Indy 500. DL, Jasmine and Willy discuss the sport of auto racing, the lack of diversity, and the future of sport in the changing times of America.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Comedian Sinbad

programme.title: Stepdads The Sketch- Ep 1
programme.desc: When infidelity claims the life of Joanne Bates, her children Lisa and Stevie are left in the custody of her fiancé Mike and his brother Jerry. Mike, a straight-laced, hardworking accountant; and Jerry, a wild, unstable, womanizer were both former foster children and together they provide a unique balance of parenting skills for young Lisa and Stevie. - Step Dads starring Ben Sloane (R.I.P.D, Alpha House), Morocco Omari (Empire, 21 Bridges, Homeland, Chicago Fire), Jorie Binion (Chicago P.D) Charles Dunlap (Chicago Fire, Empire), and Jay Davis (Not Another Black Movie, Choke On That: The Series, Not Another Zombie Movie) is a comedy about two polar opposite foster brothers raising two children using non-traditional parenting methods while shedding a satirical light on the importance of adoption. We poke fun at some of the mishaps which comes along with the shock of being a new parent, but ultimately, we hope to spread awareness on adoption, the importance of having fathers and father-figures in the lives of young people, and having a familial loving environment. The moral of our story is that “No family is perfect, but every child deserves to be loved unconditionally, and raised in a reliable, stable support system.”

programme.title: Europa
programme.desc: Discovering and exploring Jupiter's most promising moon, Europa. Europa was named after a Phoenician noblewoman who was abducted by Zeus after he had transformed himself into a bull. Rather fittingly, Zeus established Europa on the island of Crete as its queen, where he had several children with her, including Minos, the legendary king of Crete. In later ages, the continent of Europe would be named after Europa.

programme.title: Jupiter
programme.desc: Jupiter is the fifth planet from our Sun and is, by far, the largest planet in the solar system – more than twice as massive as all the other planets combined. Jupiter’s stripes and swirls are actually cold, windy clouds of ammonia and water, floating in an atmosphere of hydrogen and helium. Jupiter’s iconic Great Red Spot is a giant storm bigger than Earth that has raged for hundreds of years.

programme.desc: For eons, the cosmos has been littered with the remnants of creation. Prepare to be impacted, as we adventure into the world of asteroids & comets.

programme.title: Space Channel Exclusive- I4's Dr. Sian Proctor
programme.desc: Dr. Proctor is a geoscientist, explorer, space artist, and astronaut. She is the mission pilot for the Inspiration4 all-civilian orbital mission to space. She is also one of The Explorer’s Club 50: Fifty People Changing the World. Her motto is called Space2inspire where she encourages people to use their unique, one-of-a-kind strengths, and passion to inspire those within their reach and beyond. She believes that we need to actively strive for a J.E.D.I. space: a just, equitable, diverse, and inclusive space as we advance human spaceflight.

programme.title: My Hometown Favorites
programme.desc: New York, NY: Passionate about his city, Tony gives us an intimate tour of the New York City foods he loves - sturgeon and bagels, fluke ceviche, pan-seared foie gras, braised veal cheek, authentic cheese and, of course, a hotdog.

programme.title: San Sebastian: A Food Lover's Town
programme.desc: San Sebastian, Spain: Tony explores the food-crazed Basque culture. Tony's guide, Chef Luis Irizar, takes Tony into the underworld of Basque gastronomic societies. Later, Tony explores the city's tapas bars.

programme.title: Saigon
programme.desc: Saigon, Vietnam is an incredible place to visit. It has history, and cultural excursions, like cruising the Mekong Delta and visiting a floating marketplace. In Ho Chi Minh City you can shop until you drop, stay in five-star hotels, and enjoy an incredible culinary experience.

programme.title: Auckland
programme.desc: Auckland is New Zealand's largest city. Laura takes an hour's drive south of Auckland to a working sheep farm in the New Zealand countryside. A few miles down the road, Laura spies a familiar sight - Hobbiton, the set from the Lord of the Rings films where Bilbo lived before and after his journey.

programme.title: Athens
programme.desc: Athens is an exceptional country to experience history. First, visit Syntagma Square and Greece's famous landmark- The Acropolis. An excursion to Greece is nothing without a trip to the Agora, as we finish off by enjoying Athens’ most abundant resource- water.

programme.title: Singapore
programme.desc: The first sight is Singapore's Merlion statue. For glimpses of the wild you have three fun options where you can see exotic animals in their open (not closed) sanctuaries. Next, explore Raffles Landing for a picture-perfect view along the Singapore River.

programme.title: Naples
programme.desc: Naples exists in an incredible location at the base of Mt. Vesuvius beside the Port of Naples. Experience Napoli's castles on the islet of Megaris, Castel dell 'Ovo, Castel Nuovo, Castel Saint Elmo, Arch of Triumph of Alfonso, and the Torre dell' Oro.

programme.title: Gleneagles & Scottish Countryside
programme.desc: First, head over to Castle Rock. Then, venture down to the Royal Mile that provides fascinating insights into the region's history, and is a charming street of pubs, restaurants, and shops. Also, take a moment to revel in the glory of St Giles' Cathedral.

programme.title: Italy: Part 2
programme.desc: The brilliance and grandeur of Italy is demonstrated in five captivating settings. Feel like a tall wildflower in the sun and breeze as the hills of Altomonte billow off into the distance, sooth every aching nerve as you absorb the perfect view along the Tiber River, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Underwater Beauty
programme.desc: Fish of all stripes and fluorescence call the crystal-clear waters of Chicago’s Shedd Aquarium home. Water and light collaborate to reveal the tranquil beauty that is life underwater.

programme.title: Running of the Bulls
programme.desc: The Festival of San Fermin in Pamplona, Spain is a deeply rooted celebration of traditional and folkloric events, including the Running of the Bulls. Experience the incredible energy each morning for eight consecutive days as thousands of people run ahead of six, 2,000-pound charging bulls.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Dublin
programme.desc: At the confluence of Muir Eireann and the Irish Sea on Ireland’s East Coast stands the capital city of Dublin. Join Laura McKenzie as she enjoys the perfect pint at Gravity Bar atop Guinness Brewery, explore Dublin Castle, and become acquainted with The Four Seasons Dublin.

programme.title: Paris
programme.desc: There is more than enough to keep you busy in Paris. Historic sites such as the Louvre, Notre Dame Cathedral, the Picasso Museum, and Paris Opera House only get you started. Tuileries Garden and Paris Beach offer a unique way to relax and have fun, and Sacre-Coeur offers a 360-degree view of city.

programme.title: Los Angeles
programme.desc: Rent a Rolls Royce and roll through L.A. in style. When you hit Hollywood and Vine you know you are in the city’s heart, as the Pantages Theater, Capitol Records Building, Grauman's Chinese Theatre, and Kodak Theater greet you. Get the skinny on everything Beverly Hills and visit Olvera Street.

programme.title: Bangkok

programme.desc: There is more than enough to keep you busy in Paris. Historic sites such as the Louvre, Notre Dame Cathedral, the Picasso Museum, and Paris Opera House only get you started. programme.desc: Westward ho! We settle in Salt Lake City, where we learn about Brigham Young's settlement of the Utah territory and his monument at This is the Place Park. Then we dig in the dirt to find hundreds of perfectly preserved dinosaurs at the Utah Natural History museum.

programme.desc: Rudy Maxa knows that an adventurous safari is a wonderful way to experience South Africa. Get up-close-and-personal with lions, giraffes, elephants, and dozens of other animals in their natural habitat, thanks to robust preservation laws in place.

programme.desc: Climb the ramparts of Edinburgh Castle. Tee up at the world's most famous golf course, St. Andrews. Tour Deward's whiskey distillery. Stroll Stirling's historic battlefields of Braveheart fame. And, sail the bonny banks of legendary Loch Lomond.

programme.title: Cape Town

Where else in the world can you wake up in a cosmopolitan city, spend the afternoon with penguins, ride a funicular to the edge of the continent, and watch the sun set from a beach with a glass of wine?

Surfers brave enormous waves and exotic birds watch visitors climb serpentine paths that rise above the coast amid seaside resort towns. Also, visit South Africa's lush wine country in the village of Franschhoek.

programme.desc: Rainforests are as much a mystery as the ocean depths. Explore the most fertile, varied, and surprising ecosystem on the planet, home to plants and animals still unknown to us. What makes the rainforest so unique? The answer is often water!

programme.title: Part 2
programme.desc: As Sara becomes acquainted with her new school, her father’s fever worsens back in India, and his regret deepens. During Sara’s luxurious birthday party, she receives bad tidings that alters the course of her life forever.

programme.title: My Classic Car
programme.desc: On this episode of My Classic Car, Dennis makes his way to French Lick, IN for the Porsche Parade.

programme.title: The Law of Moises
programme.desc: Moises, a talented young filmmaker, discovers that his true destiny is to save the town that he desires so much to escape. The question Moises longs to receive clarity on is- Do we choose our dreams, or do our dreams choose us?

programme.title: Breakdown
programme.desc: With Oregon in their sights, Dylan openly challenges Brock’s decision to escape Chicago for a simpler life in Oregon. Just when smoother roads appear to be prevailing, something profoundly mysterious occurs that changes the Turner's plans.

programme.title: Breakthrough
programme.desc: When things appear to be going from bad to worse, God’s miraculous energy inspires Dylan to contemplate his depth of faith. The question is, will Brock and Dylan together discover the power that God’s love has to cast away all fear?

programme.title: Princess from the Sea
programme.desc: Moya, a tribal princess, flees her war-torn island. Two cultures unite as she helps the Robinsons build a new fortress. Ernest becomes infatuated with Moya, whose life is in danger from the dark spells of a shaman.

programme.title: Fireman Rescues Girl; Flight 811; Quarterback; The Other Boy; Acting Upon Fate
programme.desc: When an explosion blows a hole in the fuselage of Flight 811, the passengers panic, but the captain and his crew are determined to save them. A 12-year-old boy is hit by a car, but when a witness recalls the incident, they recall his guardian angel stepping in front of him and taking the hit.

programme.title: Electric Fence; Mother and Child Reunion; Dog Saves Master; Life on a Line
programme.desc: A mother and her baby were miraculously saved after being thrown overboard in a raging storm, a mysterious force stops a man from touching a metal fence that had a hidden broken power line touching it, and a dog and his owner share a special connection as the dog saves the man's life. And more!

programme.title: Runaway Hearts
programme.desc: At a poignant moment in their lives, 11-year-old Tevin and his 5-year-old sister Angel escape their dysfunctional home to live in the streets. With nowhere to go, Tevin and Angel meet two people who need a miracle just as badly as they do.

programme.title: Frozen Stupid 2: Open Water
programme.desc: When Tony’s car is towed out of Lake Houghton (again), the D.N.R. decides to hit him with a huge fine. Luckily for Tony, there is a fishing tournament the upcoming weekend with a grand prize of $20,000, and he has the boat and lure to win.

programme.title: The Boy Who Loved Trolls
programme.desc: When 12-year-old Paul's wish that the wonderful stories he reads would come true is realized, he discovers a troll and a mermaid under a bridge. It turns out that the troll has less than a day to live, and Paul must choose to risk everything to save him.

programme.title: Bridge to Terabithia
programme.desc: When Leslie Burke moves in next door to Jess Aarons, Jess finds a friend in Leslie. Over time, they discover a secret place in the forest across a fallen pine tree, and over a creek, they call Terabithia, a place where memories are sacred.

programme.title: Konrad
programme.desc: Konrad was created as a perfect “instant 8-year-old child” in a factory, but due to a glitch in the factory's computer, he is delivered to Bertie Bartolotti by mistake. When the factory realizes a mistake was made, and recalls Konrad, Konrad does not wish to leave his new family and friends.

programme.title: Paws to the Rescue
programme.desc: Upon deciding to testify against his former employer at a tobacco company, Harry Burton’s son, Charlie, is threatened by two thugs hired by the company to thwart Harry’s testimony. That is when the family’s two dogs come to the rescue.

programme.title: Cop Shot; Girls Survive Big Wave; Aussie Capsized; Deserted Baby Success; Dog Saves Boy
programme.desc: Don Mauldin had a premonition that something terrible was going to happen, and asked his wife Maggie to pray for him. Three young girls are drawn to the big surf conditions in California. A distress call off the east coast of Australia puts members of the Coast Guard on alert and in danger.

programme.title: Prayers for Theresa; Cop in a Wash; Valley Hills Vision; Jet Ski Rescue; Heaven's Window
programme.desc: Two-year-old Theresa and her family were in the process of moving into a new home when she was abducted and drowned by a teenage boy. The community rallies together. A photo taken on a field trip to Our Lady of Valley Hill in Kentucky, shows what appears to be a gateway to Heaven. And more!

programme.title: Sioux City; Dade County Canal; Lady in Green; Affair of the Heart
programme.desc: A woman is brought back to life after her car sinks at the bottom of a canal. Is a mysterious lady in green to thank for Joe Trucker's miraculous recovery? The patients of an experimental heart surgery meet and fall in love. And many more stories that prove the existence of miracles.

programme.title: Baby Comes to Life: Burning from Within; Tara's Angels; Healed by Kindness; Dannion Brinkley
programme.desc: A baby is born lifeless and declared dead, but after 78 minutes, miraculously comes to life. A Vietnam veteran is struck by lightning while talking on the phone and is dead for the next 28 minutes. After his experience he gained the ability to predict the future and communicate with the dead.

programme.title: Body Surfer; The Rosenblatt Love Story; Dream Child; Soul Sister; Dog Rescues Cat
programme.desc: A drummer is miraculously rescued after snapping his neck at the bottom of the ocean. Two girls' psychic connection may have enabled one girl to wake the other from a coma. A rescued dog gave his adopted owner a reason to live again. And many more stories proving the existence of miracles.

programme.title: River Wild; Man in White; New Jersey Lake; Twister Survival; 1,000 Men and a Baby
programme.desc: Three girls crash through thin ice into freezing water, a man tries to come to their rescue when he too falls through the ice. Firefighters race against time to save all four lives as the whole thing is caught on tape. A 12-year-old boy hiking in the woods was critically bitten by a rattlesnake.

programme.title: Miracle on Parkway; Woman in White; Heavenly Message; Doctor Brazil; Deserted Baby
programme.desc: An angel guides a fireman to a hidden exit in a nightclub fire, a miraculous coincidence saves a woman pinned under her car for eight hours, and a man with no medical experience is able to cure disease and preform surgeries thanks to the help of a deceased World War I doctor.

programme.title: The Rivals
programme.desc: David Nelson has a rival, and his name is Will Thornberry, the Nelson's next door neighbor.

programme.title: The Pills
programme.desc: Ozzie decides that he wants to go on a diet so that he can fit into a pair of size 33 pants.

programme.title: The Fall Guy
programme.desc: At first Ozzie, attempts to persuade his son David to stand up for his rights, and not allow people to take advantage of his good nature, after David has an argument with a friend. However, Ozzie quickly regrets the advice he gave David.

programme.title: Starcrossed Lovers
programme.desc: Parsons' good-hearted sidekick Ben is now a member of the Robinson family group, but David objects when he discovers that Ben is in love with his daughter Joanna. Meanwhile, Emily must act as midwife when Elizabeth prepares to give birth.

programme.title: Never Name a Duck
programme.desc: Ritchie becomes very attached to two baby ducks that were left over from a show and decides to adopt them. Rob faces the daunting task of making Ritchie understand the consequence of attempting to keep wild animals as pets that may be happier living in the wild.

programme.title: My Classic Car
programme.desc: On this episode of My Classic Car, Dennis checks out the Wellborn Muscle Car Collection.

programme.title: Thanksgiving Angel; Blind Skydiver Sees; Thanksgiving Feeding Needy; African Hijack
programme.desc: A poor mother of two can only afford to give her kids a meager Thanksgiving meal, when an elderly neighbor they had never met invites them to eat Thanksgiving dinner with her. When the mother returns the next day the to thank the woman, the apartment had been empty for years.

programme.title: God's Voice; McKay's Pennies; Doctor Rises from Ghetto; Ryan's Angels
programme.desc: A young Ben Carson turns his life around and becomes the youngest Chief of Pediatric Neurosurgery in the United States. A voice in the middle of the night told a bedridden hospital patient to "get up". She got up and was cured of her nerve disorder. And more miraculous stories.

programme.title: Starcrossed Lovers
programme.desc: Parsons' good-hearted sidekick Ben is now a member of the Robinson family group, but David objects when he discovers that Ben is in love with his daughter Joanna. Meanwhile, Emily must act as midwife when Elizabeth prepares to give birth.

programme.title: The Judge's Punishment
programme.desc: In Galilee, Jess works as a private teacher, mentoring Aviner's daughter, Elkie. Jess soon finds himself entangled in a family feud when Aviner's son, Daniel, feeling that he is being ignored by his father, proceeds to open his own, separate, business in spite of his father.

programme.title: The Miracle Maker
programme.desc: It is 14th century England amid the Black Plague when Jess unexpectedly saves Morgan, a performer at a local market, who Jess later discovers is a conman that sells fake potions to "cure" the plague. Morgan soon discovers that miracles really can happen if he refrains from spreading false hope.

programme.title: The 3
programme.desc: After the untimely death of his daughter, Jimmy finds himself at a crossroads in life. The choices he is about to make will determine the rest of his life. It is at this lowest point that Jimmy is visited by three guests, each with their own agenda, that will steer him toward his destiny.

programme.title: My Classic Car
programme.desc: On this episode of My Classic Car, Dennis travels to the Gulf Coast for Cruisin' the Coast.

programme.title: Shaytana's Eye
programme.desc: The peaceful Kingdom of Kale is thrown into chaos after the Citadel is overthrown by the dark forces of Kreel and Xax. After his family farm is destroyed by the Xaxian army, young William Tell is visited by the mystical Kalem who reveals that he has been chosen to seek the legendary Crystal Arrow.

programme.title: Swarm
programme.desc: Princess Vara has fallen ill, and the group is taken in by Harana, a healer and leader of a group called The Watchers. programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. Jim Saric and Trophy Hunter Tom Sullivan outline strategies for dealing with windy conditions to salvage your trip.

So when you have a batch of pike this big, you better know what you’re doing when you go to filet them. This week on NAPA’s North to Alaska, you’ll see how it’s done.

Of course they will roll out just ahead of a massive polar vortex. But, like this season, sometimes the greatest tests have the best payoff.

programme.title: Astypalea: Smart, Sustainable Island
programme.desc: Astypalea up until now is probably only known to insiders. The small island is located in the Aegean Sea, it belongs to Greece and is especially known for its butterflies. This is likely to change in the future: Astypalea will become a model for smart, emission-free mobility. The island wants to prove that a purely electric transport system is already possible today – without any restrictions on the mobility of its inhabitants. We explain the details.

programme.title: Audi Annual Press Conference 2020
programme.desc: 2020 was dominated by a global pandemic and great upheaval, which therefore shifted the focus even more strongly to the question of responsible actions. As part of the automotive industry, we are responsible for our employees and customers, for stable economic growth, and for a sustainable business model. Despite – or precisely because of – the current challenges, we are in a position where we can make a big difference. At Audi, we see ambitious climate targets, the paradigm shift toward software, and the impetus created by new competitors as an opportunity to play an active part in shaping the future of mobility. Our Board of Management team, which has been active in a new constellation for about a year, will provide an overview on how Audi handled the unusual year of 2020 and on which future topics we have our sights firmly set.

programme.title: Jobriath A.D.
programme.desc: Known as the first openly gay rock star, Jobriath’s reign was a brief two years. Done in by over-hyped publicity, shunned by the gay community, and dismissed by critics, Jobriath retreated to the Chelsea Hotel, where he died forgotten, one of the earliest casualties of AIDS. But years later, new fans discover his music, and acts such as The Pet Shop Boys, Def Leppard, and Morrissey cite him as an influence. Experience the heartbreaking, unbelievable story of the one, the only, Jobriath.

programme.title: Raid Of The Rainbow Lounge
programme.desc: A riveting recount of a violent 2009 raid of a Texas gay bar and its aftermath. Following sordid allegations and outrage, Fort Worth emerged a leader in LGBT equality. Experience the journey as told by the victims and those who helped change the city.

programme.title: Kalen Allen on Working With Ellen, Studying Beyoncé, and Cabin Fever
programme.desc: S1 E2 | Media personality Kalen Allen and his famous dog are in self-isolation, but they're still cracking all the jokes.

programme.title: Fortune Feimster on Hooters, The Dinah, & Being Funny During a Crisis
programme.desc: The star of the hit Netflix special Sweet and Salty joined Inside With the Advocate to share about how she's faring at home and why she's proud to be part of the LGBTQ community.

programme.title: The Drag Roast of Sherry Vine
programme.desc: S1 E2 | Cruel, harsh, tasteless. And that’s just the roastmaster. The rulers of NYC nightlife united for The Drag Roast of Sherry Vine as they read her to filth. And Revry caught it all on camera!

programme.title: The Library
programme.desc: As we seek to honor and celebrate the countless LGBTQ individuals, communities, sub-communities, and dynasties that have flourished in the face of adversity over decades, it dawned on us that there are so many unknown and untold stories about gay history, vocabulary, vernacular, and the human experiences that fuel the formation of cultures and identities based on authentic self-expression and love. As we discovered these stories, we wished for a gay “library” where anyone could visit and learn, in bite-size portions, about crucial events in gay history, gay heroes and icons past and present, fascinating sub-cultures, slang terms, scientific references, political movements... Essentially, a record of all the bits of queer education that are at risk of being lost or misinterpreted — information that we all crave as members of LGBTQ communities and as Allies. Do you know the story of the first Pride parade? Ever wondered what “Skoliosexual,” “Polycule,” or “Doppelbanger” means? The Library is open — and ready to clue you in.

programme.title: Culture Q
programme.desc: S1 E23 | We spolight queer talent Jasmin Savory-Brown in the upcoming Scream film, as well Jamie Clayton as Pinhead in Spyglass Media Group's Hellraiser. Later we sit down to chat with Chanel and the Circus, and then discuss the Texas House of Representives passing the anti-trans HB25, attempting to ban trans youth from organized sports. NFL Las Vegas Raiders head coach Jon Gruden, resigns in disgrace amid homophbic email scandal, and out player Carl Nassib takes a rare personal day to process the news. Finally, we celebrate icon and astronaut, Sally Ride who will be the first LGBTQ person featured on US currency, and congratulate Lance Bass and his husband Michael Turchin on the birth of their twins.

NFL Las Vegas Raiders head coach Jon Gruden, resigns in disgrace amid homophbic email scandal, and out player Carl Nassib takes a rare personal day to process the news. Finally, we celebrate icon and astronaut, Sally Ride who will be the first LGBTQ person featured on US currency, and congratulate Lance Bass and his husband Michael Turchin on the birth of their twins.

programme.title: The Library
programme.desc: As we seek to honor and celebrate the countless LGBTQ individuals, communities, sub-communities, and dynasties that have flourished in the face of adversity over decades, it dawned on us that there are so many unknown and untold stories about gay history, vocabulary, vernacular, and the human experiences that fuel the formation of cultures and identities based on authentic self-expression and love. As we discovered these stories, we wished for a gay “library” where anyone could visit and learn, in bite-size portions, about crucial events in gay history, gay heroes and icons past and present, fascinating sub-cultures, slang terms, scientific references, political movements... Essentially, a record of all the bits of queer education that are at risk of being lost or misinterpreted — information that we all crave as members of LGBTQ communities and as Allies. Do you know the story of the first Pride parade? Ever wondered what “Skoliosexual,” “Polycule,” or “Doppelbanger” means? The Library is open — and ready to clue you in.

programme.title: Denial

programme.title: The Millennial Experience
programme.desc: The Millennial Experience is one part dance-for-film and one part documentary. The film explores cultural appropriation vs appreciation, LGBTQIA+ culture, feminism and how these topics impact the Millennial generation. The dance sequences in the film are adapted from director Alex Crozier's stage production MILLENNIALS which focuses on the aforementioned themes. Fourteen on-camera interviews that expound on the main topics were conducted with people of various ages, ethnicities, sexual orientations, and genders . The Millennial Experience seeks to uplift the voices of women, LGBTQIA+, and BIPOC communities in an effort to create a more equitable and just world.

programme.title: Gay Positive
programme.desc: Gay Positive educates viewers about the controversial ban on queer men donating blood in the USA. The film captures opinions of people from all walks of life, asking, If you were in need of blood would you take it from a queer? Organizations are forced to reject healthy individuals from donating. During the filming of this documentary, Mexico and the UK lifted their ban, while the FDA insists it remain. Through insightful conversations with Laverne Cox, Rutanya Alda, Blanche Baker, Jim Colucci, Frank DeCaro, Trapper Felides, Tiago Grade, Carly Hughes, Chelsey Keding, Yetta Kurland, Lisa Lampanelli, Vincent Leggett, Danny Logan, Dave McRee, Anthony Lee Medina, Eric Millegan, Kaitlin Monte, Tym Moss, Garry Novikoff, Athena Reich, and Justin Luke Zirilli; Gay Positive raises public awareness on the potential benefits of lifting the ban.

programme.title: PUCCINI by Julien Lestel Company
programme.desc: Le eroine del compositore Giacomo Puccini erano quasi sempre condannate a un tragico destino. Qui vengono portate sul palco accompagnate dalle arie più belle. Questa coreografia è un omaggio all'opera, e in particolare all'illustre compositore scomparso.

programme.title: Jakub Jozef Orlinski- Il Pomo D'Oro
programme.desc: Il controtenore polacco Jakub Józef Orlinski si è guadagnato in breve tempo la reputazione di cantante dalla sorprendente padronanza vocale e dall'audacia scenica. Questo concerto riflette la tanto attesa uscita del suo primo album, Anima Sacra, un recital di arie sacre del XVIII secolo recentemente riscoperte con il gruppo barocco Il Pomo d'oro.

programme.title: S. Prokofiev - Valery Gergiev
programme.desc: Il Festival di Pasqua di Mosca è uno degli eventi di musica classica più importanti al mondo. Vi sono presenti i più grandi solisti sotto alla direzione del più rinomato direttore d'orchestra russo, Valery Gergiev, con l'orchestra del Teatro Mariinsky di San Pietroburgo, di cui è il direttore. In un ciclo dedicato al compositore Sergei Prokofiev, il pianista russo Daniil Trifonov interpreta il Concerto per pianoforte e orchestra n. 1.

programme.title: B. Philharmoniker: Gershwin Night
programme.desc: Il Waldbühne di Berlino, residenza estiva dell'orchestra filarmonica della città, i Berliner Philharmoniker, è uno degli anfiteatri all'aperto più belli d'Europa. Nell'estate del 2003, il direttore d'orchestra giapponese Seji Ozawa ha diretto la famosa orchestra su successi di Gershwin come Un américain à Paris, Rhapsody in Blue, I Got Rhythm ... Ospite speciale: Il famoso trio jazz di Marcus Roberts.

programme.title: G. Puccini: Tosca - Simon Rattle
programme.desc: Basata su un'opera teatrale di Victorien Sardou, l'opera Tosca ha conquistato il pubblico sin dalla sua uscita nel 1900. Questo dramma verista è sublimato dalla composizione virtuosa di Puccini. - Sotto la direzione di Sir Simon Rattle, la storia d'amore di Floria Tosca e Mario Cavaradossi si svolge e viene messa alla prova dal tirannico capo della polizia Scarpia, che governa Roma. In questa produzione, il famoso tenore argentino Marcelo Álvarez trascende la scena, accompagnato dalla sublime Kristine Opolais nel ruolo dell'eroina.

programme.title: Daniel Oren & Saioa Hernandez - ORW
programme.desc: L'affascinante soprano spagnolo Saioa Hernández, con la sua voce potente e ammaliante, interpreta le famose arie d'opera italiane in concerto. Questo spettacolo ci permette di apprezzare il bel canto "l'arte del canto lirico" utilizzato nelle opere dal XVII secolo. Valorizzando le capacità tecniche dei cantanti, a volte a scapito dell'espressione scenica, la voce vola come fosse un uccellino.

programme.title: Verbier Festival: Boris Berezovsky
programme.desc: Boris Berezovsky è considerato uno dei migliori rappresentanti della scuola pianistica russa, soprattutto per la sua potente tecnica. programme.title: The Magic Flute - Simon Rattle
programme.desc: Il Flauto magico è l'opera finale di Mozart. Un racconto meraviglioso, una favola popolare o un racconto che marca il periodo della sua maturità, la storia della regina della notte, il principe Tamino, il vanaglorioso uccellatore Papageno e il suo flauto magico, ha lasciato il segno nei cuori e nelle menti. Accompagnato dalla prestigiosa Berliner Philharmoniker Orchestra sotto alla direzione di Simon Rattle, il direttore Robert Carsen rivisita questo classico con un tocco raffinato attraverso una profonda riflessione sulla vita e sulla morte.

programme.title: J.S. Bach: Organ Concerts
programme.desc: Per rendere omaggio a Johann Sebastian Bach che ha servito per 27 anni come "maestro di cappella" nella chiesa di San Tommaso a Lipsia, l'organista Ullrich Böhme dà un concerto sul nuovo organo della chiesa: una replica del modello storico che suonava Bach.

programme.title: Bach and Philippe Herreweghe
programme.desc: Philippe Herreweghe, direttore d'orchestra e del coro belga, è specializzato in musica antica, in particolare quella di Johann Sebastian Bach. Qui dirige il Collegium Vocal de Gand, che ha fondato nel 1970. A Parigi, nella chiesa barocca di Saint-Roch, le sontuose voci di Grace Davidson (soprano), Damien Guillon (controtenore), Thomas Hobbs (tenore) e Peter Kooij (basso) risuonano in un programma religioso dedicato al Natale.

programme.title: Verbier Festival: Evgeny Kissin
programme.desc: Autentica star del pianoforte, il musicista russo Evgeny Kissin è ospite fisso del Verbier Festival in Svizzera, dove si è esibito più volte dalla prima edizione del 1994. La Sonata per pianoforte n. 59 di Haydn, la Sonata per pianoforte n. 32 di Beethoven e la "Melodia" di Christoph Willibald Gluck da Orfeo ed Euridice offrono a Kissin l'opportunità di mostrare la portata del suo virtuosismo e il lirismo delle sue interpretazioni, ma anche il suo carisma fenomenale.

programme.title: The Nutcracker - Mariinsky
programme.desc: Ed è proprio sul palco del Mariinsky di San Pietroburgo che, nel 1892, è stato creato il capolavoro di Tchaïkovski: lo Schiaccianoci. Sullo stesso palcoscenico, 120 anni dopo, l’orchestra del medesimo teatro, sotto alla bacchetta del maestro Valery Gergiev, accompagnata dal prestigioso balletto del teatro Mariinsky, ne offre una versione che non potrebbe essere più fiabesca.

programme.title: Denis Matsuev at Concertgebouw
programme.desc: Il pianista russo Denis Matsuev, uno dei più grandi virtuosi del suo strumento, si esibisce qui in un recital solista sul palcoscenico del Concertgebouw di Amsterdam. In programma ci sono le Stagioni di Tchaikovsky, un classico della musica russa per celebrare il 175° compleanno del compositore nel 2015, e un'altra opera romantica: La Kreisleriana di Schumann. Egli esegue anche l'impressionante e virtuosistico "Tre Movimenti di Petrushka" di Stravinsky.

programme.desc: Il controtenore polacco Jakub Józef Orlinski si è guadagnato in breve tempo la reputazione di cantante dalla sorprendente padronanza vocale e dall'audacia scenica. Questo concerto riflette la tanto attesa uscita del suo primo album, Anima Sacra, un recital di arie sacre del XVIII secolo recentemente riscoperte con il gruppo barocco Il Pomo d'oro.

programme.title: Berliner Philharmoniker: Abbado
programme.desc: Nel 2001, the Berlin Philharmonic Orchestra diretta dall’italiano Claudio Abbado suona tutte le sinfonie di Beethoven sul palco dell’Accademia Nazionale di Santa Cecilia a Roma. La Sinfonia n. 2 in RE maggiore fu scritta da Beethoven proprio quando fu diagnosticata la sua sordita’ ma la stessa composizione non ne risente in alcun modo e conferma a pieno titolo il ritmo e la dinamica musicale come elementi distintivi del compositore.

programme.title: Giuseppe Verdi: La Traviata - ORW
programme.desc: La Traviata, "La Devota", un'opera in tre atti, con un libretto di Francesco Maria Piave basato sul romanzo e la commedia La Dame aux Camélias di Alexandre Dumas fils, è una delle opere più popolari. Rappresenta la redenzione attraverso l'amore per mezzo del personaggio di Violetta. Questo ruolo, notevolmente interpretato da Patrizia Ciofi che unisce forza e fragilità, richiede assoluto virtuosismo.

programme.title: Vox Luminis: Handel in Versailles
programme.desc: È nella sontuosa Cappella Reale di Versailles che il gruppo Vox Luminis porta Georg Friedrich Handel sotto i riflettori. Specializzato nel repertorio barocco inglese, italiano e tedesco, il gruppo Vox Luminis, sotto la direzione di Lionel Meunier, esegue con leggerezza e raffinatezza due salmi, un'opera lirica e un oratorio.

programme.title: Balanchine: Jewels - Mariinsky
programme.desc: Girato al Teatro Mariinsky, questo spettacolo vede la partecipazione di alcuni dei più famosi ballerini del teatro di San Pietroburgo, tra cui Ulyana Lopatkina, Igor Zelensky e Andrian Fadeyev, accanto al direttore d'orchestra Tugan Sokhiev. I Gioielli di George Balanchine sono parte integrante del repertorio della compagnia - uno dei più grandi al mondo, sia per numero che per fama.

programme.title: Mozart Requiem - Claudio Abbado
programme.desc: Sotto la direzione di Claudio Abbado, la Lucerne Festival Orchestra, accompagnata dal Coro della Radio Bavarese e dal Coro della Radio Svedese, ha eseguito con grazia il Requiem di W. A. Mozart al Festival di Lucerna nell'estate 2012. Le voci solenni di Anna Prohaska (soprano), Sara Mingardo (contralto), Maximilian Schmitt (tenore) e René Pape (basso) esprimono la bellezza e la profondità di questo capolavoro.

programme.title: Lang Lang - Piano Recital
programme.desc: La scelta di Lang Lang per la musica e la modalità di presentazione ha affermato la sua sensibilità del XXI° secolo rendendo al tempo stesso omaggio ai suoi precedenti pianistici e ai suoi mentori. Non è stato certo un caso che abbia suonato Wanderer Fantasy di Schubert, la prima opera che il suo insegnante del Curtis Institute, Gary Graffman, aveva registrato e usato per concludere il concerto delle Réminiscences Du Don Juan de Mozart di Liszt, associato ai più grandi virtuosi del pianoforte.

programme.title: Verbier Festival: Boris Berezovsky
programme.desc: Boris Berezovsky è considerato uno dei migliori rappresentanti della scuola pianistica russa, soprattutto per la sua potente tecnica. Per il 15° anniversario del Verbier Festival, in programma un recital con la Sonata in si minore di Franz Liszt, seguito da brani di Schumann. Un vero e proprio viaggio nel romanticismo.

programme.title: Léo Delibes: Coppélia
programme.desc: Il coreografo e direttore artistico Eduardo Lao si è assunto il compito di reinventare Coppelia, utilizzando la sua versatile compagnia di 23 danzatori per contribuire con la sua personale visione. Egli sottolinea lo spirito comico di Coppelia mantenendo la partitura originale scritta da Léo Delibes nel 1870.

programme.title: Zubin Mehta - Khatia Buniatishvili
programme.desc: Zubin Mehta, direttore dell'Orchestra Filarmonica d'Israele, ha tenuto un concerto "tout en concertos" con il Concerto per pianoforte e orchestra n. 1 in do maggiore di Beethoven del pianista virtuoso Khatia Buniatishvili la quale segue il Concerto per due trombe in do maggiore di Vivaldi e il Concerto per clarinetto in la maggiore di Mozart.

programme.title: Paolo Arrivabeni - ORW
programme.desc: L'opera è sinonimo di cantanti. Eppure l'orchestra sinfonica gioca un ruolo cruciale in queste opere musicali e teatrali. L'Orchestre Royal de Wallonie - Liège, sotto la direzione di Paolo Arrivabeni, ci introduce quindi alla ricchezza della musica strumentale di alcune opere.

programme.title: Symphonic Dances: Zahia Ziouani
programme.desc: A capo dell' Orchestra Sinfonica Divertimento (fondata nel 1998, in residenza a Stains dal 2005), Zahia Ziouani è riuscita a diversificare il pubblico della musica classica. Gli studenti dei conservatori della regione dell'Île-de-France si uniscono a lei per un viaggio nel repertorio sinfonico sotto il segno della danza, dalla tarantella italiana alla farandola provenzale, passando per il gopak ucraino.

programme.title: G. Puccini: Tosca - Simon Rattle
programme.desc: Basata su un'opera teatrale di Victorien Sardou, l'opera Tosca ha conquistato il pubblico sin dalla sua uscita nel 1900. Questo dramma verista è sublimato dalla composizione virtuosa di Puccini. - Sotto la direzione di Sir Simon Rattle, la storia d'amore di Floria Tosca e Mario Cavaradossi si svolge e viene messa alla prova dal tirannico capo della polizia Scarpia, che governa Roma. In questa produzione, il famoso tenore argentino Marcelo Álvarez trascende la scena, accompagnato dalla sublime Kristine Opolais nel ruolo dell'eroina.

programme.title: Daniel Oren & Saioa Hernandez - ORW
programme.desc: L'affascinante soprano spagnolo Saioa Hernández, con la sua voce potente e ammaliante, interpreta le famose arie d'opera italiane in concerto. Questo spettacolo ci permette di apprezzare il bel canto "l'arte del canto lirico" utilizzato nelle opere dal XVII secolo. Valorizzando le capacità tecniche dei cantanti, a volte a scapito dell'espressione scenica, la voce vola come fosse un uccellino.

programme.title: B. Philharmoniker: Gershwin Night
programme.desc: Il Waldbühne di Berlino, residenza estiva dell'orchestra filarmonica della città, i Berliner Philharmoniker, è uno degli anfiteatri all'aperto più belli d'Europa. Nell'estate del 2003, il direttore d'orchestra giapponese Seji Ozawa ha diretto la famosa orchestra su successi di Gershwin come Un américain à Paris, Rhapsody in Blue, I Got Rhythm ... Ospite speciale: Il famoso trio jazz di Marcus Roberts.

programme.title: Vasily Petrenko: Dvořák - Beethoven
programme.desc: Una chiamata dal destino? Messaggi rivoluzionari segreti nascosti nella musica? La Quinta Sinfonia di Beethoven è una delle opere più esaminate nella storia della musica. Comunque la si interpreti, è senza dubbio una delle composizioni più potenti e magistrali mai scritte. Ascoltate questa sinfonia drammatica e commovente eseguita dalla Israel Philharmonic Orchestra sotto la raffinata direzione di Vasily Petrenko.

programme.title: Leonidas Kavakos And Yuja Wang
programme.desc: Due degli artisti più emblematici del Festival di Verbier interpretano insieme le opere di Brahms in un ricco concerto di musica da camera. Acclamato all'unanimità dal mondo della musica classica dal 1985, quando fece scalpore diventando il più giovane vincitore del prestigioso Concorso Sibelius, il violinista greco Leonidas Kavakos combina in questo concerto il suo virtuosismo con quello della pianista Yuja Wang, un'artista affermata a soli 26 anni.

programme.title: S. Prokofiev - Valery Gergiev
programme.desc: Il Festival di Pasqua di Mosca è uno degli eventi di musica classica più importanti al mondo. Vi sono presenti i più grandi solisti sotto alla direzione del più rinomato direttore d'orchestra russo, Valery Gergiev, con l'orchestra del Teatro Mariinsky di San Pietroburgo, di cui è il direttore. In un ciclo dedicato al compositore Sergei Prokofiev, il pianista russo Daniil Trifonov interpreta il Concerto per pianoforte e orchestra n. 1.
